;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On a certain line Joana wrote 55 odd numbers. Can you discover the sum of the last three numbers written in that line? Can you do this more generally for a given quantity of odd numbers?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Given the number N of odd numbers in a certain line, your task is to determine the sum of the last three numbers of that line.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;input&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#input&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Input&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The input is a sequence of lines, one odd number  &lt;code&gt;N (1 &amp;lt; N &amp;lt; 1000000000)&lt;/code&gt;  per line&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;output&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#output&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Output&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For each input line write the sum of the last three odd numbers written by Joana in that line with  &lt;code&gt;N&lt;/code&gt;  numbers. This sum is guaranteed to be less than 2&lt;sup&gt;63&lt;/sup&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;sample-input&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#sample-input&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Sample Input&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;3&lt;br /&gt;
5&lt;br /&gt;
7&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;sample-output&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#sample-output&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Sample Output&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;15&lt;br /&gt;
45&lt;br /&gt;
87&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
